      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RAY'S BEAUTY (1) could finish only among the minors last time (18.43) at Richmond, bringing a two run winning streak to an end. Looks well placed here and should prove hard to beat again. SIMPLY JUAN (7) goes very well this course and distance starting eight times for three wins and two minors. Was out of the placings last time (22.81) at this track in a Grade 5, finishing fifth and beaten 2.25 lengths. Looks one of the chances. JET FUEL (5) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at Maitland over 450m behind Quick Thinkin' (25.49) in a Grade 5. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. TILLY TIPPETT (2) returns here as an each-way chance.",
